PN,46102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1777551071
OL,3,C'Exhausted' Eluned Morgan says 'vote
OL,4,CPlaid Cymru' during election event
OL,6,FShe followed up in Welsh by adding:
OL,7,F"Pleidleisiwch Plaid Cymru..." meaning
OL,8,F"Vote Plaid Cymru", but corrected
OL,9,Fherself immediately to say "Plaid
OL,10,FLafur" (Labour Party), which was met
OL,11,Fwith laughs and claps by party members.
OL,13,FSpeaking to ITV Wales' National
OL,14,FCorrespondent Rob Osborne, the First
OL,15,FMinister said: "We're all a little bit
OL,16,Fexhausted, once you switch into Welsh
OL,17,Fthe word 'Cymru' comes off your lips.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/4
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
